author: @indrimirdayani8277
text: aku ingat cintaku betapa panik kau ketika beberapa menit saja aku terlambat pulang kerumah kau memelukku sambil menangis seakan kau tak ingn kehilangan aku walau sedetkpun, kau sangat takut kalau sesuatu yg buruk menimpaku, yg kau tau hanya aku selalu berada disisimu tidak keluyuran kemana2  sampai kau berkata lebih baik kita berdua di butakan saja matanya biar tidak kemana2,tidak memperhatikan hal lainnya memperhatikan dan memikirkanmu saja.

author: @indrimirdayani8277
text: kau sering berkata kekasihku, sayang seberapa dalam cintmu padaku, lalu aku berkata dalam sekali, lalu kau berkata kalau cintaku itu dalam sedalamnya tidak ada sanggup mengukurnya, besar sekali lebih besar dari langit, gunung paling tinggi pun  masih jauh lebih tinggi cintaku.

author: @indrimirdayani8277
text: ani cintaku yg sangat cantik aku sangat ingat ketika kau sering berkata memangnya itu untuk apa ya, kenapa kita sangat butuh dengan uang, sangat lama aku bisa mendapatkan jawaban dari kalimatmu itu, sekarang aku mengerti kalau artinya uang tidak bisa membeli cintamu dan juga tidak bisa membeli cintaku, cinta kita berdua tidak bisa dibeli dengan uang, cinta adalah segalanya bagimu, selalu bersama dan berpelukan erat dari pagi sampai petang  adalah harta yg ternilai harganya.

author: @indrimirdayani8277
text: ani istriku yg amat  aku sayangi aku ingat ketika kau punya cita2 yg mulia ingin menjadi ibu rumah tangga saja tapi keadaan yg memaksa kita untuk tidak tinggal serumah dulu, mungkin karna masa itu kita masih sangat muda dan masih banyak beban cita2 yg ingin kita raih, mungkin ingin mencari materi atau ingin mencapai prestasi yg besar seperti yg kau alami saat ini, tetapi itu semua masih terlalu dangkal bagimu, bagimu membahagiakan keluarga dan masyarakat jauh lebih besar, masyarakat yg jauh dari kemiskinan dan jauh dari wabah penyakit terutama di kota daeng,

author: @indrimirdayani8277
text: ani kekasihku hampir tiap hari aku berdiri di pinggir pantai aku sangat ingin menyebrangi lautan untuk bertemu kamu, entah kau berada di korea atau dimakassar tapi ada famili yg bilang kau ada di karungan, ada yg bilang juga kalau kau ada di malaysia punya kilang kereta proton sampai kilang maggie, entahlah saat ini aku bucin banget sama kamu, mungkin itu karma yg aku dapatkan tak bisa memahami betapa besarnya  cintamu padaku, aku ingat ketika kita pacaran kau sedang berada di taiwan sekolah, mama berkata tiap hari kau belajar berenang, ternyata kau ingin berenang dari taiwan ke makassar hanya untuk bertemu dengan aku, aku sampai  mau mati mendengar berita itu , aku tidak sangka sebegitu besar pengorbananan yg ingin kau lakukan demi cinta kita.

author: @ensar4278
text:
May Allah's, His Messengers, His beloved ones greetings and blessings be upon you. 

How To Perform the Uwaysi / Uways Al-Qarani (Veysel Karane) Dhikr

Preparation:

1-   Get into a silent, peaceful mood before start performing the Dhikr (not loudly, as much as you could hear your own voice).   

2-   Better to be alone ideally (when possible).    

3-   You have to be in a well-mannered and polite mood, without forgetting in whose presence you are before. 

4-    You should have performed your ablution (wudu) earlier.

5-     There is no spesific time period to perform the dhikr, you can start your dhikr whenever you feel most ready to make it and feel most available within the day. 

6-     However, ideally the best times to make the Uwaysi dhikr are either before and after the Morning Salat, and before you go to sleep at nights. Dhikr must be performed twice a day: first in the light of the morning, this means you can make it at any time during the day, and then secondly at the darkness of the night and so that means in the evening or night times. Allah says: â€œWhile everyone is in sleep; my servant mentioned Me as well as my Messenger in the absence of the othersâ€ thus Allah will love the Dhikr performer a lot. 

Performing the Dhikr: 

1-  Before you start doing your dikhr, initially recite Basmala : â€œB-ismi-llahi r-rahmani r-rahimâ€ and then you must first say: ''Tawba Astaghfirullah'' for 100 times repeatedly (alternatively you can say â€˜Astaghfirullah El Azimâ€™ too).    
 
2-      Then without saying any â€˜Basmalaâ€™, we send Salawats to our beloved Prophet Muhammad (pbuh) at least for 100 times. So you will say; â€œAllahumme Salli Ala Seyyidina Muhammedâ€, or another salawat of your choice, at least for 100 times or more than 100 repeatedly. There is no limit in the numbers of Salawats. If you would ask us, we would advice to say it minimum for 100 times. However for those who would like to make it, we can also advice for 132 though this is not essential. If you would ask why 132, please then refer to our book, Love of Uwaysi-1.

3-      Once you finish saying Salawats, you must then read -11- Surah Al-Ikhlas and -1- Surah Al-Fatihah only, these numbers are precise.  

4-   Gift Section:
And then send the Salawats and Surahs that you read as a gift to: â€œMy glorious Allah, I would like to give the rewards of the Surahs and Salawats that I have read to; our beloved Prophet Mohammadâ€™s (pbuh) mubarak soul, his Ahl al-Bayt, his friends and companions, his high family, to all righteous servants, to Al-Khidr (as) and the derwishes (saints) that he loves, to the helping sultans, and to hodjas (teachers) teaching us and to their hodjas, and to all Uwaysis, as a gift. Amen. Note that, you can also include your own relatives, friends, actually anyone that you love at the final part of the gift.  

5-      Tawhid:
Finally, Say Auzu Basmala for once (A'uzu billahi minashaitanir rajim Bismillahi rahmani Rahim), and then you must recite Tawhid, so say; â€œLa Ilahe Illallahâ€repeatedly at least minimum for 100 times, or more.  

**Please also note that, 11 Ikhlas and 1 Fatihah shall not be read once after completing the dhikr.**

Please visit our website www.veyselkarane.com for further information. We also recommend you to review our videos and subscribe to our official youtube channel: Ã¼veys academia.

author: @jo769
text:
Tiffany whenever you go, SONES will always be there for you. Korea and the world doesn't deserve you. You are a hard working, a sincere and such a thoughtful person. You have such a great voice and wonderful personality. You are a strong girl too â¤ï¸

We all know how humble and friendly you are.  Always the one bringing Soshi together and updating with us (Fans) about SNSD through your SNS. 

You gave me strength, hope and your cheerful bright smile always never fails to make me smile and brighten up my day. I love your character, your friendliness, your helpfulness, your always giving and understanding attitude.

This is precisely why you are my first idol, my ultimate bias since 2010 and will always be. You and SNSD are the ones that brought me to K-pop and if you are leaving, I am also leaving.  

And lastly, Tiffany. You are my inspiration, my aspiration, my motivation, my purpose, my morale support, my role model and my hope.
Loving and supporting you to the end of time since 2010 â¤ï¸

author: @Shiku82
text:
Hello, Miss Hwang. I just wanted to say what, I'm proud of you, being Fanytastic and SONE since I'm a little girl. I thank you for this album, for this video, for this song. I want to thank you for being the strong woman you've always been, an example to follow, a piece of diamond that no one can break. I really love the music you create, it relaxes me and takes me out of my stress and bad days. For us, the fans who know you and know how much you have put your love in this, really, for all of them I thank you. It continues, grows and shines. You are the person for that, because, God will protect you from all the hatred of the world, you, loving girl and with a smile.
Thank you for always protecting members, for protecting and encouraging Taeyeon. Really, you're an angel, just because you're golden inside, you shine on the outside.
Thank you for always treating your fans with love, even when you are tired and have been disrespectful to you, turned against you and have spoken words of hate. I, all the Fanytastics around the world are proud of you, because, you have done the right thing and we trust that you will continue doing it. We will be with you in the good and the bad, I will pray for your well-being every day, because we love you, I love you, and you have made us happy for a long time. You are a person dedicated to your work and from YouTube, instagram, Twitter, whatever it is. We will give you support, because we are a family and we call ourselves SONE.
Now, forever and ever. We love you, Tiffany. Thank you very much for your album, for your smile, for being.
God bless you, babe.

author: @llseeinnm603
text: I'm pretty fed up with this whole "scandal". Tiffany is American, born in San Francisco, raised in LA. She was born 44 years after the end of WW-II, but only 2 years after the end of the Park and Chung dictatorships. That 15 year period of Korean history was marked by the brutal suppression of demonstrators, including mass shootings of students, and the imprisonment and disappearance of thousands of political opponents. Koreans seriously need to reflect on their own history, before they condemn an American citizen who has been one of the strongest supporters and proponent of Korean culture. Makes on wonder if there is such an ideological difference between North and South!

text: The first thing that crossed my mind after seeing what she posted was " baby girl you fucked up real big this time " , quite an unforgivable mistake considering the fact it was almost Independance day , with that said , such a mistake will get consequences and harsh criticism , totally acceptable ! Now moving to something else , being into the Korean culture for almost 12 years of my life and knowing the people and studying  the history pretty well although i'm neither Korean nor lived that past , i'd have to say , THEIR ANGER IS UNDERSTANDABLE and when i say " THEIR " i mean the PUBLIC CITIZENS OF SOUTH KOREA not KNETZ !! Knetz are well known for being harsh and cruel to everyone regardless of their position in  the industry , but what to do ??You can't fight them all right ? What matters is what the public thinks of her , and trust me Korea is like any other country , has GOOD and BAD people too , so to say  " oh i no longer like Koreans for what they're doing to Tiffany " is kinda wrong ! They're sensitive people , close-minded ( not in a bad way , as in more traditional and old school type of people ) believe the media whole heartedly , and they're still not used to the International wave they're getting the last few years because Kpop !!! Nice people though , most of them .......... THIS IS ALL OBJECTIVE ....... Now , enough talking about the good , let's talk about the bad side , Kpop industry is LITERALLY DEVILISH , as most of fans know ; how idols are trained ,  how they're treated , how they're supposed to  behave , a small mistake could lead to a major career loss !! The most irritating thing i hate about Koreans though ( bad ones , as in Knetz and their brothers ) despite all what idols go through the way they criticize them is something i cannot acept  , "you did wrong , you're the worst person on earth and that's it " no forgivness no nothing . They are the main reason behind every celebrity suicide and then they blame it on depression ....... i hope this whole issue die soon though before something bad happens to her !!!

author: @JohnKim-mk3fv
text: I think many of you are getting this Tiffany's flag issue wrong.  Although she does not deserve death comments and what she did was a mistake, you need to understand the issue from a different perspective.  First of all, you cannot compare this issue with Tzuwu's flag incident, or GD's.  Expressing gratitude using the rising sun flag is a seriously hurtful act for all of Koreans.  Why so? Because of the following reasons:  Undeniably, all of this is in the past and Tiffany is not in the war-torn (who did not live through the war and seemingly has no idea about the modern East Asian history) but seemingly in a peaceful era where people get to communicate and appreciate other people's cultures.  It seems as if many things have worked out between South Korea and Japan, but there are still things lingering.  Consider a rapist and a victim.  Japan's army is the rapist (I know this sounds harsh but in reality, it was a lot more harsh than this - google if you want to find about the accurate East-Asian history) and you are the victim's grand child (Tiffany, Taeyeon, or all of Koreans).  After many years the rapist gets sentenced, fined, and made guilty by the judge (United Nation), he pleads guilty and everything seems to be ok.  However, after serving time and repent, the rapist makes outrageous statements saying the victim wanted to have sex and did so voluntarily totally debasing the victim and her family (In very recent years, Japan made official statements about Comfort women being volunteers, so the issue is not from war-torn 75 years ago).  The victim and her family get infuriated and demand justice from the K-police (Korean government).  K-police contacts J-police (Japanese government) and work out a shady deal without consulting the victim and her family (Japan pays Korea 1 billion yen or 8.3 million usd to clear this issue of comfort women in December of 2015, and the settlement funds still haven't reached the victims).  Now the J-police demands K-police to remove the rapist's criminal record (Japan demands the comfort women statue to be removed from the Japanese embassy in Seoul).  Since the shady deal, officially now the victim and her family cannot demand justice if the rapist happens to accuse her of volunteer sex (Korea cannot demand any kind of apologies after this deal).  Now the victim and her family are desperately reaching out to other people for what happened (Comfort women, not just Korean women, and their helpers are working hard to let people in the world know what happened.  THIS IS STILL HAPPENING.)  Second, Tiffany is a face that represents South Korea in entertainment industry.  As a representative of her country, she should have been more mindful of sensitive history issues and whatnot.  Although Tiffany's mistake seems to be a simple mistake and does not deserve death comments, because of all of these reasons, many Korean people feel Tiffany and the like (AOA members) need to be made an example of why celebrity or any person representing a country need to know their country's history.  One last thing to say: people harshly bashing Tiffany because of what she did please stfu.  A young girl made a mistake but she doesn't deserve to have her career gone over this.  People advocating Tiffany by bashing Korean people, please stfu.  You don't have an in-depth idea about why Korean people bashing Tiffany.  The best thing to say is put yourself in the rapist's victim shoes then you will understand Korean people.

author: @israelmatunan8742
text: I really don't understand why k-netz are so angry over Tiffanys mistake. My country is also colonized by Japan. They've raped and violated our women. The Korean soldiers that they've brought with them also raped and violated our women, even more than the japanese did. They've killed and tortured our people. They've destroyed our homes, forcing our people to live in caves and forest just to hide from the japanese. They made our people live everyday of their lives in fear.They've made our country their battlefield against their war with America, thousands of our innocent people caught in the crossfire and destroying our major cities. What's worse is the Bataan death March where they've forced 75,000 of our people and american troops to walk 65miles going to prison camps without food, water and rest, while continually abusing them physically. 10000 of our people died in that march. Even my own grandmother experienced the terror brought by the japanese, they were forced to hide for days in holes they've dug up whenever japanese soldiers goes in their town. But despite everything that they've done in our country and in our people we don't hate the japanese, we don't give a fuck even if a citizen of our country, even if they are a celebrity, uses the japanese flag or the rising sun flag in their social media post. Why? Because it's all in the past already, it's all history. What's done is done, what's lost is lost. We should'nt dwell on the past and the past should'nt control the present. It's right to celebrate liberation day, to honor the dead and the victims, but it's wrong, really wrong, to torment a sweet little woman just because of a single unintentional mistake. It's not like she's a murderer or a drug pusher or a plunderer or a corrupt politician but they treat her like one. It's not like her mistake caused a death of someone. What can they possibly gain from tormenting her? Do they feel pleasure by watching her suffer? Do they enjoy destroying her life and hardwork just because of one mistake? She already admitted her mistake, apologize for it and repented for it, what else do they want? I believe that the act of tormenting her, badmouthing her, hurting her, destroying her life and career, treating her like an international criminal are far worse than the mistake that she had committed. K-netz are really the best at criticizing other people like they are perfect, like they are Gods, like they've never comitted mistakes in their life. I just hope that Tiffany will be ok after all of these craziness ends.

author: @Kiirze
text:
About the issue. Well, sadly, her apology wasn't accepted at all. K-netz want more as they think it wasn't sincere enough. I do believe it was, she wrote it after a 2 hours flight at the airport surrounded by the members. I'd like everyone to not deny her sincerity. What is worse is that they believe that Tiffany is some japanese imperialist who hates Korea which doesn't make sense at all. I agree she made a mistake and should've been more careful. Not defending her actions but as a person. She already realized it, deleted the snap in two minutes after posting it and apologized afterwards. She knows it and we all know she didn't intend to offend anyone. So what I don't understand is how this honest mistake is UNFORGIVABLE. Like, she didn't kill someone or didn't say "I support Japan." Fuck Korea." while she went there all by herself without her family and dedicated around 15 years of her life for that country. And k-netz comments are just beyond cruelty. They basically want her dead, mentioning her mother, be raped and kicked out of Korea. This is going too far right now and no human being deserves such treatment. Everyone makes mistakes. I can't imagine how she must feels right now. She's probably blaming herself, having the mindset that litterally a whole country is hating her for a careless mistake she didn't mean to do. This could easily lead to suicidal thoughts and I hope she's not reading these comments. As a fan, it's upsetting that all you can do is sitting there watching the media twisting facts, mocking her and waiting for miracles.
We're all hoping for better days now.ï»¿

author: @faggotsmoker9588
text:
Here's my opinion. I think she should be criticized about being so incautious. She lived long enough in Korea to know about how Koreans feel about their colonial period in Japan, and as a celebrity on a national scale, she should've cared more about Koreans' political views. However, I don't detect any malice in her actions. She simply wanted to show her affection toward Japan after having a good time with Japanese fans in the concert. And after all, she's an American. It would be even more uncanny if she cared just as much about Korean history as regular Koreans did.
And it's such a shame that a lot of fellow Koreans can only express their patriotism through rejecting other non-patriots. She might not be a true-Korean, but I still think she should be allowed to work in Korea regularly like she should to do. I just think she should be more cognizant about herself. 
But of course, most people will just close their eyes and cover their ears....

author: @unicornsandicecream5713
text:
Okay lol this is gonna be long but I feel like I needed to put it out somewhere so...

Okay so I've been watching Jessica and Tiffany interactions when English comes up in interviews and in variety shows and things.... at first, even though Tiffany is my bias, I got extremely annoyed at her. I was like "really, can't you see Jessica might want to add something here" or "you're not the only native English speaker fany~" 

but then idk I guess I realized she doesn't do stuff like that on purpose. It seems like Fany is just naturally really talkative and bubbly and, as the kind of "mother" of the group, that she needs to take care of the other members if they don't know English very well. She'd be one of those friends that I'd really look up to. I'd be annoyed with sometimes, but I'd look up to her because she would know that I would be too shy to say something or not sure how to reply in interviews,etc. She would help me out and just be positive in situations that I doubt I could ever be positive in. 

.....and so thats where I kind of see Sica's possible perspective. I know shes kinda icy and cold at first, but actually a really sweet, talented person. Looking back on older videos, it seems like Sica was always a bit shy or kind of introverted. Don't get me wrong, she had times when she was having fun and being crazy... but for the most part shes on the shy-er side. And sometimes I forget they've both known each other for so long. I thought that maybe PART of why she was angry at SNSD members (because they kicked her out (?- we dont know anything for sure...)) would be because of years of Tiffany kind of overshadowing her, especially in some of the biggest opportunities they had in New York during The Boys era. but I just thought that maybe there was some hidden resentment or something. Like they really loved each other and were friends but had moments when they just didn't go well together and fought alot. Honestly, I don't know them so I have no idea. But thats just what I felt.

Now, though, its like I don't think that was it. I think Jessica never hated her for how she was because she knew it was just Fany's personality and that she had good intentions. In fact, I'm probably the one looking at some videos and then making some deep analysis when I've never known them personally lol... 
idk. I just feel like they were so close. Really. Like they were born in the same hospital, when to school together for most of their education, and then knew each other long before they were trainees, trained together, debut together...Some little interviews wouldn't torn something like that apart. And actually, neither would problems with fashion careers and whatever else. I guess what I'm saying is that I had doubts about their bond. I shouldn't have, but I did. And then after thinking it all through i was like. Dang, I don't really know them and we only see like half of their lives so who am I to be coming to negative conclusions. And from what we know about their relationship, its more likely that they are ACTUALLY really close to one another. Sisters. Somehow more than sisters. Like some deeper, stronger bond. And thats why it confuses me about why Jessica left and people believe that SNSD kicked her out?

I don't want to bring this topic up and have people get into arguements (if any1 ever reads this lol) but that just doesn't make sense to me?? especially because of all that stuff I just mentioned about tiffany and jessica. But idk.  I just wanted to bring up how I think that they are still friends. Really. Even now that they are both doing their own things. Jessica DID say she kept in contact with some SNSD members still..I'm betting one of them is Fany :) 

Either way, I will support both of them and all of Girl's Generation. Dang so sorry, this is like a freaking essay. Also, the fan wars and stuff going on in the comment section ugh, really?? can't we all just be loving and supportive. <3 <3

author: @thelocter
text:
I Just Wanna Dance is one of the best Kpop albums of the last years and one of the best SM albums released in music quality,

I dear to say that IJWD album is even better than "I" album, 
The songs of the album are super catchy and good, there's no boring songs on this album and you can play it on repeat all day long. 

Tiffany's vocals are perfect!, she sounds super good and her live singing was 100% on point!

IJWD is killer!, the choreo is super cool and all the production was super simple and classy but at the same time perfect and fun.

Tiffany really really shocked me as a solo artist, she's following her own path and that's what i like from her the most.
she won't let SM to control her career or music.

And HeartBreak Hotel is such an amazing song, seriously this IJWD bonus track aka smstation song is super good.

Go for that American market i'll support you no matther what! :) GO TIFFANY, FIGHTING

text:
Seriously, Maomao? Honestly, I'm a fan of Jessica since Gee, as has always been the most I liked among them (not only because she's beautiful, but I liked the voice and personality), but this fandom made me angry. They're different genres of music, we can't compare. I liked the two albums, and I know that both endeavored to please us, the fans.
Seriously, SONE? Hate Jessica only because of fandom? For God's sake, stop it. You may not like us, Maomao, but can't blame Jessica for it. You were also very bad with her at times, but I don't hate Fany because of this.
We'll only support the two and make them feel loved by fans, â™¥. I'm sure it's not nice to open your Instagram or read comments and find a tremendous fanwar. If you like more than one, who cares? It all depends on taste.
Eternally giving support to Tiffany and Jessica.

author: @KetchyInsomniaBuddySone
text:
From: 8 years SONE
To: You. Yes,, YOU

Dear HATERS"FAKE FANS" and IMMATURE FANS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Just shut the ** **,, dont try to provoke us to fight each others!

29 Sept, i do remember that day and how my heart broke when my bias kicked out. Until now i still hope that someday, i will wake up in 30 sept 2014 and start the morning like there was nothing happen except my excitement for SOSHI next big concert "TOKYO DOME". but that impossible T,T it wasn't a dream, it's real that she is no longer part of Soshi... for SM.

and you know what the worst part?
hey!! it was during "The Best" Album. ARRGGHHH!!!, INDESTRUCTIBLE? DIVINE? what the hell happend exactly T,T

i become a SONE in 2008, i know Soshi because of Yoona and fall in love with Sica Voice (ITNW). after 5 years, exactly in 2013 i already prepare myself if someday, one or more members became inactive. i already prepare myself if someday, one or more my sister will meet their love and married. i already prepare my self if someone leave the group for good and the rest member will give a happy farewell. BUT i'm not ready at all if it's all about "GROUP BREAKDOWN".

"8 and 1 in my eyes, but always 9 as 1 in my heart". i said it to myself, trying to forget and rejecting the fact. it's not easy guys. i cant choose "SICA ONLY", because without SOSHI i dont think i'll know and fall for her. and i cant choose "SOSHI ONLY" because without Jessica, i dont think i'll become a SONE. then what can i do? FINE, i'll support both of them.

FOR IMMATURE FANS : 
2007, 2008, 2009, 2010, 2011, 2012, 2013, 2014, 2015, 2016? which year you became a fans? how much you know about SOSHI? how much time you spend for them? how much effort and love you have for them? think again!!! you are nothing if you compare yourself to me. at least i was with them when the world still BLACK for SOSHI. you dont know how we struggling to raise PINK ocean wave. you know nothing and now you said you are a true fans? hahaha, dont make me laughing. bro and sis, SOSHI and SONE is a Family, if you hate one of your family member then you must learn more and start asking yourself, "is it right for a family to destroy their own family"?

FOR HATERS'FAKE FANS
THANK YOU SO MUCH for coming here. Just take my thanks because you deserve for it! why? whats the reason? HELL YEAH, you help us to increase the view. Once again, thanks for you effort in this past 9 years(almost). keep your spirit and dont forget to come here everyday. thanks guys!!!! we'll also wait you in the next MV.

DONT F*CK UP WITH MY 9 SISTERS or you will drowning in our Pink Ocean Wave, oh!!! one more  dont forget that now we also have a Golden Color in our family.

"no matter what happen in the future, once Soshi, then we will forever Soshi, even if we married and become an old lady" (i didnt said it, the girls said it by themself)

"8 AND 1 IN THE WORLD EYES, ALWAYS 9 AS 1 IN OUR HEARTS"

TAEGANG UNITS, GORJESS SPAZZERS, SUNSHINERS, FANYTASTICS, YURISISTABLES, HYOHUNNIES, SOOYOUNGSTERS, YOONADICTS, SEOMATES

Forever9, always9, the power of 9.

author: @TreadstoneOperative
text:
*OT9 fans who are still thinking that by supporting Jessica, you are supporting SNSD, have you woken up yet? Take a look and see for yourselves. Weeks of insults, abuses and name-calling for Tiffany by maomaos. Most of the maomaos will simply use your support to leverage even more hate against SNSD and you are helping them to get there.*

*Some of you are confused about the entire notion of "Real SONEs will support all nine.". That was based on the original assumption that SNSD finally retire honorably and gracefully to assume individual activities and SONEs will be there to support them as individual artistes. However, this is not the case for Jessica because she was dismissed from SNSD and therefore stripped of further honors as SNSD from 30 Sep 2014 onwards.*

*Jessica is now an artiste for a rival company and every single cent and achievement she earns can be potentially used against SNSD, as we can see from here. It's not going to stop here. We will continue to see maomaos attacking any of SNSD's upcoming individual activities, group comebacks or solo debuts.*

*OT9 fans, it's time to come to your senses. Jessica is no longer part of SNSD and therefore SONEs are no longer obliged to help her in any way. She no longer addresses her fans as SONEs but maomaos so OT9 fans are deluded by their own emotions of being unable to let go of her. Let her go and forge her own path by her own means now.*

*SNSD is eight now.*

author: @noface_shizun
text:
I don't get people replying to comments like "I like Jessica/Tiffany's song better" saying "Fuck no, this or that is better !". People are human, they're bound to compare things and songs sung by two girls who were from the same group, more so if they came out at the same time. That's like one person comparing dark chocolate and milk chocolate: it's a matter of tastes. People don't have to go around forcing their opinions on people. Because they are just that, opinions. If people didn't have that, the world would be fucked up.  
So what if Jessica's fans were fucking douchebags or antis (not even fans of them) trying to start fanwars. What if Jessica was a liar (or something I don't even know and I don't freaking care). Legitimate opinions are about the songs and not the singers. People are freaking immature hating on the singers because of their fans. I don't go around hating the wrong people. "Jessica's fans are douchebags so I hate Jessica." What would that make of you ? A better douchebag ? Man, that's like basic common sense. Seems like fans are just so biased they end up blind. Yeah yeah I know,  Singer's fans are pissing you off so you have to piss them off. Grow up. Be the bigger person for fuck' s sake.

author: @riffgroove
text:
I finally got my copy of Tiff's wonderful album a couple of days ago and have been listening to it non-stop.
     I really wanted to congratulate Tiffany and SM's songwriters who picked a musical style that fit our pink monster so perfectly. Whereas Taeyeon's "I" was much more contemporary sounding, Tiff's album is more dance-able but mature sounding.
    Being a woman now, it wouldn't make sense for Tiffany to do cutesy, bubble-gum Kpop anymore and they picked a great sound for her.
   Favorite tracks are IJWD, What do I do and Once in a Lifetime.

    Tiffany has been so good to us over the years. Most importantly, she's *never stopped* being good to us.

   I, for one, am extremely proud of her. :-)
Great job, Tiffany

text:
This is what Jessica's Said in the interview

Understandably, she was a bit cautious about mentioning Girls' Generation andÂ SM EntertainmentÂ at first. Â She started off with,Â "I'm not sure what to say," but then opened up with her affections for her previous group, stating, "I wouldn't be here without Girls' Generation. Â If there were no Girls' Generation, there would be no me. Â Also, Girls' Generation would not be here without the company. Â It's very precious. Â I have no desire to deny who I was at the time."


Regarding the process of her departure, she said, "There was no choice but to make that decision. Â Our interests were different. Â We had to separate at some time; I just think that my time of departure came first."Â In relation to some of the negative viewpoints, Jessica said,Â "If there's any misunderstanding, I will resolve that at any time. Â The truth will go through in the end, and when time passes, I believe [people] would come to recognize [the truth]."


She was also asked about debuting as a solo artist at the same time asTiffany. Â She said,Â "I heard her music and saw her MV. Â It was very cool. Â I thought how it expressed greatly what Tiffany wanted to do. Â I hope she does well. Â As for competition? Â Our colors are too different. Â We came out at the same time unintentionally, but our music and our individuality are different. Â I think there's a fun in seeing our different charms."

author: @sp1nrx
text:
K-POP is so fascinating because of the fan base of each group. The amount of love & hate displayed in the comment sections is beyond reality.

 How anyone can *hate* - and hate is a very powerful state of emotion - someone they have never met or dealt with, even after seeing them on stage or a video, is a measure of your own self-esteem. You hate XXX exactly why? Oh, they interrupted your dream music act or they can't dance as well as others, or they're loud, or they have ambitions outside of their public life? Reasons like this show that *YOU* need to work on yourself, on working towards *your* dreams and goals, not letting others dictate how you do it and, most importantly, not wasting energy hating.

K-POP is a business and if you think or wish your life would be as glamorous, famous or having thousands idolizing you, you are not moving in that direction. People who do are aren't dreaming: they're *DOING* and only those who do can understand that this is all a business of *entertainment* not of granting dreams.

Work towards your dreams without hate or misplaced love and you will be a happier person who isn't compelled to publicly announce love or hate towards people you don't even know (and I can assure you that you really don't know these people other than what they share with you).

author: @Back2BackLakers2010
text:
http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/7377520/tiffany-i-just-wanna-dance-charts-girls-generation-solo?

The 26-year-old sees her debut solo release I Just Wanna Dance enter multiple charts as the EP soars in at No. 3 on Billboard's World Albums chart as well as No. 10 on the Heatseekers Albums chart, which sees much fewer appearances from K-pop acts.

Additionally, the EP's title track is No. 10 on the World Digital Songs chart. Meanwhile "What Do I Do," a standout cut from the release which came in both Korean and English renditions, is at No. 14 on the tally.

author: @AJZoomerFIT
text:
Let's be honest over here... You ppl need to stop all this comparisons between Tiffany & Jessica camps. There's no need for name branding, bashing others based on different opinions. Considering my bias is Tiffany, whom I've always preferred her vocal tone to  Jessica's (which sounds nasal at times) After watching both videos, I guess point goes to Jessica, sounds contradicting but it's the truth, like it or not! To say am I bias - NO, disappointed - YES! Why - should Tiffany had released a different track from her album such as 'What Can I Do' to be her debut, she would've killed the charts, which saddens me becoz 'I Just Wanna Dance' isn't a good choice for a debut release which doesn't showcase any of her vocal range and power. 

By comparing number of views between Jess & Fany isn't fair - while Fany still in SNSD, automatically reached out to the wider SNSD fan base, cannot be compared to Jessica, completely now on her own, under a different company. In fact, Sone fans need to be aware that Tiffany, still under SMTown, now saturated with much stiffer competition amongst other artists, who's breaking out as solo artists.... Tiffany is in much danger considering the saturation of artists, I am afraid SM Management will focus much spotlight on her, compared to Taeyeon. (Have u thought about that), whereas Jessica doesn't face much competition or lack of attention in Cordial. Jessica's trash-talk over at her video was caused by the negative comments over Tiffany's, (out of spite) behavior is very obvious. U oughta grow up.  

Looking at some of the comments made (understand no doubt there're those who truly likes it, that's fine) But reading those saccharine sweet comments that are sugar-coated with over-praising how good the song is, blah, blah, which I claimed those as blind followers... C'mon how can y'all call yourselves fans with the continuing bashing against one another and trash-talk towards Jessica. Considering myself a Tiffany supporter always, a true fan should always be upfront and honest when comes to opinions of songs. Do not confuse constructive criticism as negative comment, as much we all wish for Tiffany's success, feedback & encouragement are necessary to help her learn from mistakes so she'll make better albums in future. Keep on fighting! Peace I'm out. x

author: @Sweetoholic
text:
I normally do not like Tiffany's voice. I'll always give things a try but it usually makes me cringe. I can't explain it... Not to hate on her, she could always sing but her voice was never my cup of tea... It just always seemed too flirty? I can't put my finger on what exactly it was about her voice...

But this. Honestly, I was very surprised. I did not think I would enjoy this at all... I actually prepared to cringe lol. But this song is absolutely amazing. I don't know about the rest of her album, but these are the vocals I would expect from someone who has been singing for as long as she has been. She shines more here than she ever did with GG or TTS. I'm actually considering purchasing it. Congratulations on your solo debut!

text:
I don't get how people can say she doesn't deserve a solo. Like who are you to say? Just because she "didn't perform well" on this stage or just because her music isn't your cup of tea you think u have the right to say that? All you see is this but u don't know how much she trained, how much sweat and tears sacrificed, going through so much emotional stress for the past 10 years. While you are partying and enjoying youth, she is practicing her butt off just to get a chance to debut under gg. So who are you to say she doesn't deserve it? Everybody deserve a moment to shine on their own.

And for Christ sake, SHE LOOKS UP TO TAEYEON AND HER VOCALS. she is not here to outshine taeyeon. Stop comparing both of them. 

And for people that thinks this is a flop. 
#1 in 13 countries
#9 in US itunes
#1 on 7 digital charts
30,000 over copies sold on Hanteo
If you don't like it doesn't mean it's a flop.

You've worked hard ppany-yahhh<3

author: @xxshinrai
text: Tiffany is so gorgeous in this MV and her vocals are so lovely. However, overall I felt like the song sounded too chilled out for the lyrics of 'I just wanna dance the night away'. I'm sure this is up to personal preference and interpretation but I would have liked to see Tiffany's vocals soar and let loose and really shout from the rooftops.. because the phrase itself is a way of expressing how much you want to let go and let loose after experiencing stress or frustration. That being said, I still enjoy the song's arrangement and concept for what it is. It's really easy to listen to and a nice summer track.

author: @shinigamiabarairenji
text: The song is cool but honestly it wasn't what I was expecting from Tiffany at all. I was expecting something more R&B-ish that shows off her vocal ability more, something similar to "Holler" or "You Think" and obviously I was expecting the MV to be way more glamorous. If you watched The TaeTiSeo, you know that Tiffany put in a lot of work on the MV for "Holler", picking sets and clothes that were super stylish, etc, so I was thinking it would be the same with her solo debut. I wasn't expecting her to be wearing gym clothes and dancing in an empty parking lot with backup dancers that looked a bit man-ish for my taste. It's not that I don't like it, it's just very surprising if you've followed Tiffany and saw her personality (at least the one she showed on TV and such) throughout the years.

text: *LMAO.* All these "music critics" and "music experts" need to seriously explain how this song is "lacking" or "boring". They just simply say the song sucks and thats it. Like uh....are you trolling or just be a plain hater? People would take you more seriously if you gave constructive criticism instead. Just because this song is different from typical "k-pop style" people say its "boring".....NEWSFLASH!! Not every song needs extreme vocals or beats! author: @fitnessdiary1654
text: To all those saying that the song sucks...This is not a typical kpop song you get to hear, it's full of Tiffany's style and everyone can tell it. The fact that she chose to release something SHE LIKES rather than the public will like alone is applaudable. She is releasing something that shows who she is and is establishing her own music style. It is recognised by k-netizens as well and I have seen their comments that they appreciate Tiffany for trying something that she truly loves without trying hard to appeal to the public. Whether one likes this song or not is a matter of personal taste, I didn't like it at first but now I am in love. What's important for a singer is to establish her own style and Tiffany certainly did it. This song suits her and I am pretty sure she is the only one in SNSD who can pull of this song. Everyone has their music style. Taeyeon's I suit her really well and Tiffany probably can't handle that song, but Taeyeon won't be able to pull IJWD off as well. What matters is they found their style and let's just appreciate Tiffany's effort:)

text: Being a Sone fan, I always adore Tiffany's voice. As much I really want to like this song but after hearing a few times I honestly can't say I'm really captivated. Nothing to do with her voice but I juz dun feel the same wow factor as Taeyeon's 'I' did when it first released. Guess it's the song choice, and im not sure i quite like the dance choreography on this video which the energy seems lacklustre. Either a kickoff power ballad to showcase her vocal power or an upbeat fun song would make for her debut... I know the die hard supporters will say positive things no matter what.. As I strongly urge those who keep raving how good it is, to be truly honest that this track could measure up to 'Rain' or 'I'? i feel bad for Fany coz her manager oughta be shot for choosing this as her first single debut... sigh.

author: @fz_dracohart1255
text:
I'm a SONE and....I'll lie if I say I love this song :/ Oh nononononono I DON'T hate this! This piece is rather refreshing actually amongst the heavy edm-dubstep trend in k-pop nowadays, and this kinda reminds me to the 90's pop song(?). What putting me in rather dismay is the song is rather...bland? We know repititiveness in a pop song isn't new, but this song sounds like too repetiting and kinda flat and the lack variety of melody is rather a turn off. Thank goodness Tiffany's awesome voice make this track somewhat bearable (In fact her voice is the only good point of this song). Do I sounds like bashing Tiffany? I hope you don't see it that way, because in fact I'm worried for her. Her voice is beautiful but this title track of her solo debut doesn't explore much of her vocal potential. I pray this solo debut of hers won't flop....

I'm complaining about the song, you see. It almost seems like the composer amd lyricist isn't doing their best in the song. I haven't listened to other tracks so actually it kinda rude to predict how well her solo debut will fare. I really really wish other tracks and cover up the weakness of the title track. And oh, I can't wait to listen to What Do I Do! Composed by Tiffany herself and lyrics by the Sooyoung, I bet it'll be great! 

Somehow I actually hoped for a ballad (or slow rock-pop) for solo releases for the vocals, because imho such genres can give them a chance to express their vocal prowess better. But to each of their own, I guess... I just find it personally appealing for vocals to sing the genre outside pop, the main genre of their group or the mainstream genre of the k-pop in whole.

P.S I think I forgot to mention how beautifully bootyful Tiffany here huhehehehehehhehe

text: Personally, I expected this song to have that 'spark' like Taeyeon's I. I'm not comparing the both of them, they are both amazing singers, I'm comparing the feel I got between the two songs. Tiffany is a wonderful singer, whose vocals, I feel, could have been emphasized more on. There were climaxes here and there, but not one that gave me goosebumps like the other songs Tiffany has sang, perhaps because of the same repetitive tone throughout the song. Again, I'm not trying criticizing her, being a sone myself, this is my opinion, and I believe that everyone is entitled to their own opinion, be it to your liking or not.

text: If SM were to release a song into the American/Western media world this would be it. The Boys flopped in the US because it lacked a lot of the Western beats and vibe while this song has a very Western feel to it. It's relaxed in a way that I could jam out to it in my car while I'm coming to/from work or it could be played in the club. I think that's why some people don't like it. It's not what you normally dictate as Kpop and not something GG would typically release. But I like it. I like it a lot.

author: @BowChickaism
text:
lol when i was done listening and watching the music video i expected people to be loving this song in the comments, i found its nature very interesting.. but i found that there were a lot of complaints/disappointments. i was shocked.

 i actually never really knew who tiffany was until my friend showed me this song 'cause they've been trying to bring me into kpop, but i'm glad i checked this video out. this is by far the most worthwhile track i have listened to in a while from kpop and the video's cinematography is pleasing to the eye.

i do not understand all this 'it's not catchy' or 'this does not stick with me' business happening in the comments, mostly because the catchier i have found a song, the easier it is to kill. other tracks my friend has recommended to me i find too generic or redundant after a while, however this i believe is extravagant enough in its composition and execution that you're able to listen to it many times and discover something new each time.

i am also most used to songs which have integrated different styles and i am compelled to mention that as a kpop song, this has done so quite well -- something to the likes of Wonder Girls' "I Feel You".

as an inexperienced k-pop fan but avid listener of differential archetypical music, i must say i am intrigued by Tiffany's track and hope that people furthermore listen with open ears. i found this song to be one of the best korean pop tracks i have listened to (at least so far through the recommendations i have received) and look forward to her career in music.

author: @renatamora1457
text: I don't follow snsd or anyone from the group specifically so I really tried to watch this video neutrally, since I don't really think much of Tiffany or many to the snsd girls. I can't quite tell what it is but this song needed something. I think a lot of people agree that this song needed a rapper to give it THAT kind of vibe. Also, when you hear the title "I Just Wanna Dance", you don't exactly expect to hear complex lyrics or anything like that. So I think this song also lacks depth in it's lyrics as well. And while the choreography is GOOD it's nothing spectacular, I don't know much about dancing, but I think any human with a brain and the ability to identify patterns can tell that this choreography isn't anything new... in fact, I've seen many of these dance moves done by f(x), so the dancing feels kind of bland, but I'm glad the dancers look like they're enjoying what they do and that they keep casting dancers of different ethnicity. Finally, I think the music video in general, at least the visuals, were also kind of lacking because we've seen what SM could do with visuals (I mean with NCTU and Press your Number and Rain). You sort of have your typical girl in a swimsuit, on a bed, wearing five different outfits and looking pretty next to something related to water. In my opinion, SM could have done better with the visuals. So with all this, you probably think I don't like this song right? That's actually not true... while there are some mistakes that pretty BIG, the song is at least pleasant to listen to (sort of like 4 Walls) and Tiffany looks so different, it's hard not to ignore how she basically captures your attention for 4 min where everything is pink. It was a good video, I'm glad I saw it, I think it shows potential for Tiffany. It's not AMAZING but it's fine :)

author: @fsdjify
text: This might not be a type of song to ranks the first place in music charts. But the concept/mv/music are not the ones you can see from GG's music and it expresses Tiffany so well. As a fan, that is all I want.  I went to her showcase yesterday and her stage was unbelievable (the song is much better with the dance choreography). Tiffany also said, all she wants is to enjoy her music with her fans rather than winning the first place at music shows. After the stage, she was sweating all over and before even catching her breath, she asked how it was. The fans shouted "the best!" "thank you" "I love you" and she started crying. Seeing her tears, I could feel how this girl put her everything into this music and I was so determined to put my every effort & support for this as well whether her choice was right or wrong.

text: I find it annoying how everyone is comparing her solo debut with Taeyeon's and putting it down. Both are really catchy and a good reflection of the artist. Taeyeon is more introverted and "I" captured the essence of herself and her experience. IJWD really shows the American side of Tiffany and her appreciation and passion for music, thus wanting to dance. I like both songs because I think they really manage to sum up the artists in their first proper solos and not something you would really see from SNSD as a group :) I think we should all just appreciate the thought and hard work that went into both their debuts rather than comparing them because they are quite different ^^

author: @Brenda-tv8tx
text:
Honestly, everyones entitled to their own opinions. No one like every type of music out there, and even I have moments where I don't like some songs from my favorite musicians. But this,  I actually really like it. It has Tiffany's footprints all over it. From the pink clothes and effects, to the music clashing with both western and korean style of pop, it screams Tiffany from every angle you look at it. And that's what I love about it, the authenticity of the artist. Okay, sure maybe SM didn't give Tiffany total control, but I like how you can identify that this song, (haven't heard the rest of the album so can't judge the rest), is a TIFFANY song, just like you would do with Taeyeon, and in the future Jessica. She doesn't have to be your bias to support her, she isn't mine when it comes to SNSD, but I'm really happy for her, it's a great song, at least to my ears. 

(ps: was I the only one who noticed she changed knee pads during the video, around half way in during the dancing-in-the-parking lot scenes).

you did well tiffany omg I'M SO PROUD
 let's be tifantastics together <3

Tiffany's been my ultimate bias for a long time, although I had many problems to choose (Yeah, I'm looking at you, Wendy). I know how she is and behaves, I know the hate she always gets and of course, I know many of the mistakes she commited (As everyone does). 

However, the point is that I can get you're not hyped or freaking excited about this like I've been and I am. I get that this doesn't have Taeyeon's vocals nor Hyoyeon's dance, but the way she's trying hard to learn, the way she works and puts all her effort to achieve such a challenging choreography for many people is something to take into consideration. I'm not telling you to like her and the song, just don't spread the hate.

And if you're excited about it like me, then really enjoy it and look forward her lives, a long promotion is waiting for us. Saranghae, Tiffany. Fighting!

author: @addrianeperez353
text:
I had this phase where I didn't like Tiffany cause I I got caught with other people tiny and subtle comments about her being sometimes too much of a perfectionist or fixing every little thing and how she somehow wanted attention. I don't really remember it anymore cause it was a short phase anyways.

But that hate faded when I looked for videos of her and stuff and I started liking her, being all positive, supportive, loving and hardworking. Even if she is deemed "the laziest dancer" (as a joke of course but still isn't the greatest), you can see how hard she tries because she's aware that she wasn't given the natural ability to dance like she is able to sing. 

She's gone through so much and I kinda regret not liking her even if it was for a moment, but at least I learned to love her and every other member. She gave up a normal life, had to be away from family and friends, and lost someone so precious to her. Like, how could you hate her knowing all of that? She even learned Korean (which is pretty hard especially is you're fluent in English [in this case her] cause the sentence structures are different and etc.) and now she has her own album, even if it's mini.

I am nothing but an avid fan but I feel so proud. After the numerous things she's faced, now she is a part of one of Korea's best groups that is known worldwide, and has finally released her feelings through music. Us SONEs will always be here supporting each and *every* member (even Jessica...for me at least).So goodluck with your solo debut Tiffany~ Dance as much as you need if that's what makes you feel free~

She's so gorgeous oh my gosh!! The song sounds very Madonna like or It's like a slow tempo "I wanna dance with somebody" Whitney Houston. The only thing that bothers me is how the title sequence thing looks so.... amateur? SM Usually has really good Title thingy but it looks like it was made from a Word Doc and it was copied and paste. I don't know why it bothers me but it just does. I keep laughing for some reason.

author: @alyssarachelle9935
text:
GUYS THE VIEWS COUNT IS FROZEN!! (or is that just my laptop??)

on a side note... about this mv and song, its not the typical 'kpop music vibe' but thats okay because its TIFFANY'S SOLO not girls generation and I think people should learn to see the difference between the two. Tiffany's solo is her chance to step out of girls generation's music and create her own.

We all know that most of the time when Tiffany is given a chance to pick a song and sing on stage she always picks english songs (ex. The way, Umbrella, Call me maybe etc) so shouldn't we all know by now that 'Soloist Tiffany' won't give us the 'kpop vibe', plus I love that about her because she is showing us her Cali girl side and making this song all the more her own style!

Lastly, I'm proud of Tiffany for earning this solo and hope she continues shine brighter than ever!! Love the whole album and I'm sure many do as well!!
Fighting, Love! <3

Ps. Stop comparing!

author: @JayRr_83
text: This is a great song and if she releases an English version of this song, it could seriously get radio play in the US. Her tone and vocal style works better with Westernized music then kpop. Like Ailee, if western audiences could get over the fact that they are Asian and get over the idea that just because an artist went through a rigorous training system known as "The Machine" that they are just as talented as the people who post videos on YouTube and write their own music. Talent comes in many forms regardless if its manufactured or natural, it should all be appreciated. Congrats Tiffany and like Taeyeon before you, you worked hard and quietly waited until it was your time to shine and now you are able to do the kind of music you want with the support of a powerful entertainment company! Bravo and I look forward to what you do in the future.

author: @Momoxoelf
text:
Whoa. I am just so proud of Tiffany and SM as whole. 

SM been on a roll lately, music- and artistic-wise, with all their releases, comebacks and debuts. And talk about aesthetics! Oh my god. Been stanning SM since 2010 and I should say, there must be some kind of creative revolution happening inside their management. 

Never thought I'd see this day where SM reaches this level of artistry. I'm almost tearing up. I know they're not totally there yet but I can see they're getting there. And that's great. 

Here's hoping SM consistently delivers from now on and continue to do right by their artists and the music. Hopefully, they'll get to that level in the future (and I'll surely be looking forward to it.)

Anyway, congratulations to Tiffany for an already successful solo debut!!! <3

author: @chuamiki129
text:
You know what? I'm delightfully surprised by this. Tiffany is bubbly, but also sentimental; I expected her to deliver something either incredibly upbeat and jumpy or a ballad, but this is nice. This is a side of Tiffany I had yet to see, and I think it's amazing. We can't expect Tiffany's music to be SNSD's music, and it is just terribly unfair to compare her music to Taeyeon's or any of the other girls', because they're showing us their individuality, not SNSD as a whole. It's not about who is better, it's simply about seeing them as an artist. So congratulations to Tiffany for achieving that, because she truly is unique. That's the feeling I get from this: she's unique.

On a side note, you adorable little booger, we know you can't dance <3 <3 <3

author: @AndreggvilJammer
text: I'm not a SONE, but I have always been a fan of SNSD, and I found this solo debut a bit disappointing. Before any bashing happens, I wanna clarify that I think Tiffany's capable of much more and her solo should be a big opportunity for her to display her vocals. Though I like this style of music, and I really think it suits Tiffany, I was expecting her to showcase more of what she - as a vocalist - can really do (because tbh not many of SNSD's songs give her a chance to do that, and even then it's only mere glimpses of her vocal potential). I know many people question her position as a main/lead vocalist, and I believe she has the potential to become a great one and she deserves her place as SNSD's main/lead vocal (as much as other people like to believe she doesn't, SM must have placed her there for a reason and SM does have high standards), so I'm hoping her B-side tracks will be able to prove all the haters wrong. Hope to see more from her; lots of love and support from an ELF! <3

As I said I am not a fan so I dont know her personality but I do think he fits the style of the song. I also have seen comments stating that this song doesnt show her vocal range. I agree that USUALLY solos have a powerful vocal and even though powerful vocals are very good, I am more into these kind of soft vocals. Very easy to listen to.

author: @theramenbucket
text:
For me, SM is creating a huge gap from other companies when it comes to experimental music. Analyzing SM's songs this year: experimental. They are following a certain direction. I think SM is trying to avoid the common Korean pop feel. SM's musical experiments turn out to be very good. A few mistakes would be noticed.  SM's songs doesn't sound the same as before. They are itching the need to evolve. This is like what I thought after watching LSM explaining about entering into the New Culture Technology. They are so open-minded and wouldn't even mind to take the risk in doing a different style. That's what making SM so powerful when it comes to music production. Also, analyzing SM's art direction in the "New Culture Technology" direction: on point. They are visually representing the song's 'everything'. I don't know how to explain but SM is just so good at aesthetics. 

--
We all have our personal tastes. Whatever you think about this, it's your opinion. I respect you. hehe :)

I give this:
Music: 8.5 / 10
MV: 9.5 / 10
Total: 9 / 10
<3 Good Luck Ppani Ppani! <3 Love you!

In an unbiased criticism, this is too bland and simple for Tiffany, both song and MV though I couldn't say much about the mini-album since I haven't heard it yet as of this writing but based on the preview I've heard, the other songs seems really good. Now back to this song, I feel that Tiffany could have done much better. If she wasn't just rushed (maybe? Or maybe she and the crew were pressured of the rumors and the fans' hype for her solo debut?) maybe she could have done much more better.

While this song and Taeyeon's I are different in genre, I couldn't feel the same pride I've felt the first time I watched and listened I. Maybe because Taeyeon's solo debut was much anticipated? But this was also very anticipated; we've been waiting since last November. I did not feel anything when I watched and listened this video. I did not feel the hard work and sincerity she and the crew they have put into this song and mv. The song somehow does not connect to Tiffany. Everything just made me confused and annoyed.

The MV has a bit of a story... but that's it? Compared to the other MVs from Red Velvet, NCT U, Ryeowook, Yesung, SM STATION mvs, what have you done? Don't get me wrong, it's fine. I'm not saying it's bad as I know there are much worse there (And SM with a worse mv?) But just comparing this MV to recent MVs released over the last few months, it's a bit eh.

But enough negativity. The dance is amazing! I love the back-up dancers (are they Americans?) and it seems that we're going to see her lie down on the stage floor! Haha, but really... that was so sexy.. I did not expect that at all from Tiffany who has always been innocent and a choding~ 

Perhaps my expectations were too high but we're talking about TIFFANY FROM GIRLS' GENERATION. She is a wonderful, beautiful and talented girl, I am sure she could have done more. But oh well, we get what we get. And, this is just her debut yet. Let's just see what she'll give us next time. 

- These are my unbiased opinion. I am entitled to have one and you may also have but let's just respect each other's opinion.

author: @JD-fz3hy
text: Honestly, I don't like this song. I liked it because Tiffany's vocal performance is so good and the visuals are nice but this track really underlies for me the issue which SM and the K-Pop industry has with female singers. This sounds like something I would have heard a decade ago on the radio, its not current at all. The songs which many Korean girl groups sing are far too safe and just not experimental enough, in the end they all start to sound a bit the same. Of course there are exceptions, I Got A Boy and Catch Me If You can were both unexpected in the ways they pushed new ground for GG. This song does nothing new though. GIVE ME DIFFERENT, GIVE ME NEW, GIVE ME FRESH.

author: @tigerlilyem-o9s
text: Wow! This is probably not the type of song that a lot of sones usually listen to. This is definitely another level, in a positive way! This song needs a deeper understanding of music genres and quality. This is not probably catchy to some people, but if you listen to it well, though, you'll realize how good the quality of the music is. The vocal is amazing, too! Looks like that Fany has worked hard to improve her vocal and singing technique. I think this is the message that Tiffany wants to convey. She wants to deliver a quality music, the kind of song and genre she likes. She is being honest to herself. She wants to show her color and taste. If that's actually the case, I think Tiff did a great job! Well done and good luck, Love! For the fans, please take some times to enjoy this moment and appreciate her work. :)
